HEADWORD: Echometry
<hw>E*chom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧chom⟦eacute⟧trie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of
measuring the duration of sounds or echoes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art of constructing vaults to produce
echoes.</def></p>

